Hails Fayose’s roles A former governorship aspirant of the People’s Democratic Party(PDP) Kayode Adaramodu has described the emergence of Hon Bisi Kolawole as a candidate as a morale booster for the party ahead of 2022. The PDP chieftain promised to make his political machinery available in ensuring a resounding victory in the governorship poll. Impostor Conducted PDP Ward Congress In Ekiti – Group… Tension In Ekiti As PDP Governorship Aspirants Reject Ward… While Congratulating Kolawole for the victory, Adaramodu said the PDP now has what its takes to win the June 18 Governorship poll. In the statement issued by the Kayode Adaramodu Campaign Organisation, the PDP chieftain also congratulated former Governor Ayo Fayose and Emmanuel Udom-led Governorship Primary Election Committee on the peaceful and successful conduct of the election. He stated further that the impending takeover of rein of government in Ekiti State by the PDP has raised the hope of the citizens. He admonished other Aspirants to respect the will and wish of the party delegates as they rally support for the PDP towards the June 18 Governorship election. According to him,” Ekiti State PDP has all it takes to win the coming election if we approach it as a team. He, therefore, called on the winner to reach out to all stakeholders and enlist their support for the general election. Adaramodu promises to make his team available to work with other stakeholders in the party in ensuring that Otunba Bisi Kolawole of the PDP becomes the next Governor of Ekiti State.